            <h2>Design Inspiration</h2>
            <h3>SharePoint</h3>
            <p>We borrowed proven enterprise concepts from SharePoint:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Master Pages</strong>: Reusable layout templates</li>
                <li><strong>Web Parts</strong>: Modular components (we call them Modules)</li>
                <li><strong>Permission Levels</strong>: Fine-grained access control</li>
                <li><strong>Hierarchical Pages</strong>: Parent-child page relationships</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Oqtane CMS</h3>
            <p>We took inspiration from Oqtane's modular architecture:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Module System</strong>: Plugin-based extensibility</li>
                <li><strong>Theme Support</strong>: Customizable visual appearance</li>
                <li><strong>Modern Stack</strong>: Blazor and .NET</li>
            </ul>
            
